question
Write the isZeroInArray function that takes the arr array as an argument and returns true if the array contains at least one zero element, 
and false otherwise.
Example:
the isZeroInArray ([20, -26, 0, -12]) function must return true;
the isZeroInArray ([2, 9, 0, 0]) function must return true;
the isZeroInArray ([1, 2, 3, 4]) function must return false;
the isZeroInArray ([1, -1]) function must return false;
the isZeroInArray ([]) function must return false.

solution:

function isZeroInArray(arr){
  let count = 0;
  for(let i = 0; i < arr.length; i++){
    if(arr[i] === 0){
    count++;
    break;
    }
  }
  if(count === 1) return true;
  else 
  return false; 
}
